    {
      "id": "news_3",
      "title": "Venture Global (VG) Soars as Geopolitical Tensions Fuel Natural Gas Rally",
      "source": "Yahoo Finance",
      "link": "https://finance.yahoo.com/energy/articles/venture-global-vg-soars-geopolitical-210724730.html",
      "summary": "Venture Global (VG) Soars as Geopolitical Tensions Fuel Natural Gas Rally",
      "full_text": "Venture Global climbed by 12.7 percent week-on-week, as investors rotated their portfolios into energy stocks amid the surging prices of oil and gas driven by escalating geopolitical tensions.\n\nAs of Friday, Bloomberg data showed that August Henry Hub natural gas futures traded up by 1.85 percent to $2.91 amid concerns over tighter global gas supplies.\n\nCrude benchmarks also jumped sharply. Brent climbed by 4.59 percent to $88.10, while West Texas Intermediate increased by 4.48 percent to $82.49—both at their highest levels in about a month.\n\nThe latest surge in energy prices was sparked by the renewed tensions between the US and Iran.\n\nOn Friday, Kuwait—one of the world's 10 largest oil producers—said that Iran damaged a power and water desalination plant following a missile attack, sparking a fire that affected a large number of its electricity-generating units.\n\nEarlier this month, President Donald Trump signaled the collapse of Washington's temporary ceasefire with Tehran, which could have paved the way for a permanent peace deal, saying in a social media post that the US has reinstated the Iranian blockade in the Strait of Hormuz after Iran allegedly violated the ceasefire terms by continuing to attack or threaten commercial ships and conducting military operations despite the agreement.\n\nIran, which sits along a chokepoint through which roughly 20 percent of the global crude oil supply passes, said that it holds authority over the waterway.\n\nLatest available data on Marine Traffic said that a total of 57 transits were recorded in the Strait of Hormuz last weekend, versus 130 daily before the conflict began.",
      "published": "2026-07-19T21:07:24Z"
    }
  ]
